Mourinho lavished praise on his match-winner, admitting he is keen to hand Drogba another 12 month deal when his current contract expires in the summer.

‘He’s remarkable. First of all he’s a team player, after that, he’s one of these with an old days mentality,’ said Mourinho.

‘He’s not selfish, not vain, a humble guy who plays and fights for the team.

‘Is this his last season? I don’t know. It must be his decision. He came here to stay, I want him to stay, the club want him to stay.

