‘The important thing is he is here and will finish his career with Chelsea. It looks, for me, that he’s going to stay doing other things when he finishes his career.’

Meanwhile, Mourinho insisted Chelsea’s comfortable win over Tottenham proves his side can cope without Diego Costa.

The Spain internationals was suspended for last night’s clash, but the Blues hardly missed their first-choice striker as Drogba produced a virtuoso display.

